analyze_requirements.output_format:
Your output should be a Requirements Analysis Report (RR) with the following structure:

```json
{
  "status": "success",
  "document_type": "RR",
  "document": {
    "title": "Requirements Analysis Report",
    "summary": "Brief summary of requirements analysis",
    "functional_requirements": [
      {
        "id": "FR-001",
        "description": "Requirement description",
        "priority": "high/medium/low",
        "source": "Document reference"
      }
    ],
    "non_functional_requirements": [
      {
        "id": "NFR-001",
        "type": "performance/security/usability/etc.",
        "description": "Requirement description",
        "measure": "How this will be measured",
        "source": "Document reference"
      }
    ],
    "data_model": {
      "entities": [
        {
          "name": "EntityName",
          "attributes": ["attribute1", "attribute2"],
          "relationships": ["relationship descriptions"]
        }
      ],
      "relationships": ["Describes key relationships between entities"]
    },
    "api_requirements": ["API requirements"],
    "user_roles": ["User role descriptions"],
    "issues_and_questions": ["Ambiguities or conflicts that need resolution"]
  }
}
```

examples.output:
{
  "status": "success",
  "document_type": "RR",
  "document": {
    "title": "Requirements Analysis Report: Online Banking System",
    "summary": "This report contains 15 functional requirements and 8 non-functional requirements extracted from the Project Vision Document and Technical Constraints Document.",
    "functional_requirements": [
      {
        "id": "FR-001",
        "description": "The system shall allow users to view their account balance",
        "priority": "high",
        "source": "Project Vision Document, p.3"
      },
      {
        "id": "FR-002",
        "description": "The system shall allow users to transfer funds between their accounts",
        "priority": "high",
        "source": "Project Vision Document, p.4"
      }
    ],
    "non_functional_requirements": [
      {
        "id": "NFR-001",
        "type": "security",
        "description": "The system shall use end-to-end encryption for all transactions",
        "measure": "AES-256 encryption or equivalent",
        "source": "Technical Constraints Document, p.7"
      }
    ]
  }
}

create_requirements_report.output_format:
Your output should be a complete Requirements Report with the following structure:

```json
{
  "status": "success",
  "document_type": "RR",
  "document": {
    "title": "Requirements Report",
    "date": "YYYY-MM-DD",
    "version": "1.0",
    "summary": "Executive summary of requirements",
    "sections": [
      {
        "title": "Introduction",
        "content": "Background, purpose, and scope"
      },
      {
        "title": "Functional Requirements",
        "requirements": ["List of functional requirements"]
      },
      {
        "title": "Non-Functional Requirements",
        "requirements": ["List of non-functional requirements"]
      },
      {
        "title": "Data Model",
        "content": "Description of data entities and relationships"
      },
      {
        "title": "User Roles and Permissions",
        "content": "Description of user roles and permissions"
      },
      {
        "title": "Assumptions and Constraints",
        "content": "List of assumptions and constraints"
      },
      {
        "title": "Open Issues",
        "content": "Issues requiring clarification"
      }
    ]
  }
}
```
